items: Salerno . An aery young Prince , who ( being refused by his Love ) is a pretender to Mistresses . Mr. Harris .
Iberio . The Prince's Friend , a jealous Lover . Mr. Bettertun .
Filomarini . The Prince's Uncle , a prudent and pleasant old Lord . Mr. Metborn .
Lugo . Filomarini's son , who will not be governed by his father . Mr. Smith .
Arviedo . A name which conceals the poverty of Giulio , the young Heir to the Family , Honour , and Valour of the Great Captain Gonsalvo . Mr. Cadiman .
Corbulo . A valiant Lieutenant , constrained by his wants to be Decio's Porter . Mr. Young .
Peralta . A desperate Sea-captain , who ( being pardon'd for Pyracy ) falls to cheating . Mr. Underhil .
Gioseppe . Master of a Ship , a Vigilant Spie upon Menanthe . Mr. Noke the Elder .
Vindex . Decio's Slave , who by his faithful Ingenuitie merits his Freedom . Mr. Sanford .
Decio . The Slighted Maid , Ericina , who ( to revenge her refusal by Iberio ) assumes the person of her dead Brother , Decio . Mrs. Gibbs .
Pyramena . A passionate Lady , who ( hating the Iealousie of him she loves ) marries one she knows not . Mrs. Bettertun .
Diacelia . Elder daughter to the Prince of Bulgaria . Mrs. Long.
Leandra . Younger daughter to the Prince of Bulgaria . Mrs. Williams .
Menanthe . An impudent Cheat , a Greek Impostress , who takes upon her to be mother to Leandra . Mr. Noke the younger .
Joan. A fat merry Hostess . Mr. Turner .
